1
00:02:52,800 --> 00:02:55,960
Someone who loves herself
as much as you do

2
00:02:57,480 --> 00:03:00,080
doesn't know how to love
or care about anyone else.

3
00:03:03,400 --> 00:03:06,680
What is Peekul Jaiaree to you?

4
00:03:06,760 --> 00:03:07,840
Peekul was my girlfriend.

5
00:03:07,920 --> 00:03:10,560
Then do you know Peeraka?

6
00:03:16,320 --> 00:03:17,520
Mr. Dharn.

7
00:03:17,600 --> 00:03:19,840
<i>Don't visit Dharn again.</i>

8
00:03:19,920 --> 00:03:21,040
This is an order.

9
00:03:23,880 --> 00:03:24,800
How did you get in here?

10
00:03:24,880 --> 00:03:26,760
Stay away from Fahsai.

11
00:03:26,840 --> 00:03:29,280
We deal with Dharn first.

12
00:03:30,040 --> 00:03:34,560
That stupid story about Fahsai and Dharn
has to end once and for all.

13
00:03:44,880 --> 00:03:47,040
Oh, Mr. Dharn.

14
00:03:48,080 --> 00:03:51,960
After the incident, will you continue
working with the Fahsai Foundation?

15
00:03:53,600 --> 00:03:54,560
Of course.

16
00:03:55,080 --> 00:03:58,680
This incident made me realize how serious
the issue of violence against women is.

17
00:03:59,560 --> 00:04:02,080
But next time,
we'll have to be more cautious.

18
00:04:03,200 --> 00:04:06,200
<i>So that means you're not</i>
<i>backing down at all, right, sir?</i>

19
00:04:07,800 --> 00:04:09,440
Smooth moves.

20
00:04:10,040 --> 00:04:11,400
He's good.

21
00:04:18,120 --> 00:04:19,720
<i>Ms. Fahsai is a great colleague.</i>

22
00:04:19,800 --> 00:04:20,640
HOT NEWS

23
00:04:20,720 --> 00:04:22,840
<i>I'd regret it if I didn't get</i>
<i>the chance to work with her.</i>

24
00:04:25,880 --> 00:04:29,280
<i>Does this signal</i>

25
00:04:29,360 --> 00:04:32,040
<i>a political alliance between your party</i>
<i>and the Namchat Thai Party</i>

26
00:04:32,120 --> 00:04:34,760
<i>in the future?</i>

27
00:04:36,440 --> 00:04:39,440
<i>Or will the connection</i>
<i>between you and Ms. Fahsai</i>

28
00:04:39,520 --> 00:04:41,960
<i>unite things first?</i>

29
00:04:42,040 --> 00:04:46,680
<i>Or maybe the parties aren't united yet,</i>
<i>but the individuals are, sir?</i>

30
00:04:48,440 --> 00:04:50,240
<i>Mr. Dharn is blushing.</i>

31
00:04:50,320 --> 00:04:51,720
<i>Wow, he's really blushing.</i>

32
00:04:51,800 --> 00:04:55,720
<i>Well, with questions like these,</i>

33
00:04:55,800 --> 00:04:58,480
<i>let me put it this way.</i>

34
00:04:58,560 --> 00:05:01,720
<i>Ms. Fahsai and I are good colleagues.</i>

35
00:05:04,200 --> 00:05:07,200
<i>Really? Is that so?</i>

36
00:05:09,240 --> 00:05:10,600
<i>I'll admit it.</i>

37
00:05:11,120 --> 00:05:12,760
<i>I admire Ms. Fahsai.</i>

38
00:05:13,600 --> 00:05:15,200
<i>And I'd like to work with her again.</i>

39
00:05:16,240 --> 00:05:18,960
<i>We already have a project</i>
<i>under consideration.</i>

40
00:05:19,960 --> 00:05:23,840
<i>But as for anything else,</i>
<i>I'll need more time to answer that.</i>

41
00:05:23,920 --> 00:05:28,120
<i>So you're not denying</i>
<i>the "unity" allegation, right?</i>

42
00:05:30,640 --> 00:05:32,120
<i>Let's not go that far yet.</i>

43
00:05:33,080 --> 00:05:36,720
<i>Right now, I don't even know</i>
<i>if Ms. Fahsai still wants to work with me.</i>

44
00:05:39,080 --> 00:05:40,120
<i>But</i>

45
00:05:41,080 --> 00:05:42,960
<i>I'll just say this.</i>

46
00:05:43,480 --> 00:05:45,400
<i>I hope we can work together again.</i>

47
00:05:47,640 --> 00:05:49,160
<i>Wow.</i>

48
00:05:49,240 --> 00:05:50,280
<i>Alright.</i>

49
00:05:56,640 --> 00:06:00,080
I SUPPORT THEM
THE TWO PARTIES ARE ABOUT TO UNITE

50
00:06:00,160 --> 00:06:02,000
MS. FAHSAI IS SO LUCKY

51
00:06:02,080 --> 00:06:03,480
I HOPE THEY GET TO DATE FOR REAL

52
00:06:03,560 --> 00:06:05,800
DON'T SAY TOO MUCH. THEY CAN SUE YOU

53
00:06:07,360 --> 00:06:09,960
I ship them so hard.

54
00:06:10,040 --> 00:06:13,680
- Mr. Dharn and Ms. Fahsai are so cute.
- Yeah.

55
00:06:20,680 --> 00:06:21,520
Here he is.

56
00:06:22,960 --> 00:06:25,280
May we get an interview?

57
00:06:25,360 --> 00:06:27,920
People are shipping
Ms. Fahsai and Mr. Dharn.

58
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:30,520
Since they're from opposing parties,
will that be a problem?

59
00:06:30,600 --> 00:06:34,080
What do you think as her brother?

60
00:06:35,120 --> 00:06:38,480
I'm surprised everyone
is so interested in this.

61
00:06:39,480 --> 00:06:40,920
There's nothing going on.

62
00:06:42,360 --> 00:06:45,240
Let me answer on my sister's behalf.

63
00:06:45,320 --> 00:06:48,960
She's just doing her job for the people.

64
00:06:49,040 --> 00:06:50,200
That's all.

65
00:06:50,960 --> 00:06:54,240
So you're denying
any relationship between them?

66
00:06:54,320 --> 00:06:57,600
That's because they're just colleagues.

67
00:06:59,440 --> 00:07:01,120
And as I said,

68
00:07:02,240 --> 00:07:05,880
the Fahsai Foundation
won't continue working with Mr. Dharn.

69
00:07:05,960 --> 00:07:08,760
We have many urgent projects to focus on.

70
00:07:10,120 --> 00:07:13,280
What about political cooperation?

71
00:07:15,960 --> 00:07:19,240
Our ideology remains the same.

72
00:07:20,240 --> 00:07:24,240
We will not be involved

73
00:07:24,920 --> 00:07:27,560
with parties
that have different principles.

74
00:07:28,160 --> 00:07:30,040
- Thank you.
- Excuse me.

75
00:07:30,120 --> 00:07:32,600
- Wait.
- Excuse me.

76
00:07:32,680 --> 00:07:35,800
- Excuse me.
- Will there be any change?

77
00:07:39,120 --> 00:07:41,200
How could you give that interview?

78
00:07:43,320 --> 00:07:46,400
Do you want people
to support Dharn even more?

79
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:51,280
And you'd rather let them
keep spreading rumors about Fahsai?

80
00:07:53,280 --> 00:07:54,600
From what I can see,

81
00:07:54,680 --> 00:07:57,480
they didn't say anything bad about her.

82
00:07:58,320 --> 00:08:00,200
They're just imagining things.

83
00:08:01,160 --> 00:08:02,480
That's the point.

84
00:08:03,360 --> 00:08:06,360
I don't want people
shipping her with Dharn.

85
00:08:09,880 --> 00:08:12,480
That's why I have to talk to you.

86
00:08:15,160 --> 00:08:18,160
Dharn spoke respectfully about her.

87
00:08:18,240 --> 00:08:20,920
But you came across as controlling.

88
00:08:23,720 --> 00:08:26,240
Young people these days
are obsessed with rights.

89
00:08:29,040 --> 00:08:31,760
Our party already has fewer
young supporters than theirs.

90
00:08:31,840 --> 00:08:34,440
You need to be more careful
with what you say.

91
00:08:39,360 --> 00:08:41,679
You usually have better control than this.

92
00:08:44,400 --> 00:08:46,600
Don't let your sister cloud your judgment.

93
00:08:54,560 --> 00:08:57,240
Then you should've handled
the interview yourself.

94
00:08:59,560 --> 00:09:00,480
Don't forget.

95
00:09:01,840 --> 00:09:05,120
This party has come this far
and you've become a minister

96
00:09:05,760 --> 00:09:06,760
because of me.

97
00:09:06,840 --> 00:09:08,120
Samut!

98
00:09:22,600 --> 00:09:23,520
Mr. Samut.

99
00:09:24,640 --> 00:09:27,280
You have an event
with Ms. Maysa this evening.

100
00:09:28,640 --> 00:09:30,040
I'm going to Heaven's Club.

101
00:09:53,880 --> 00:09:55,080
Whoa.

102
00:09:55,880 --> 00:09:57,440
I've been calling so much
my fingers are about to fall off.

103
00:10:04,200 --> 00:10:06,120
Oh? The event's about to start.

104
00:10:06,200 --> 00:10:08,040
Is Mr. Mahasamut still not here?

105
00:10:13,320 --> 00:10:16,000
He's busy. He'll be here soon.

106
00:10:16,760 --> 00:10:17,640
What's the matter?

107
00:10:19,760 --> 00:10:22,960
I heard the staff are worried

108
00:10:23,040 --> 00:10:25,480
that your boyfriend might not show up.

109
00:10:26,560 --> 00:10:29,600
They might have to move us
to last instead.

110
00:10:30,720 --> 00:10:32,880
We didn't prepare for that.

111
00:10:36,400 --> 00:10:38,920
I'm just concerned for you,
so I came to check.

112
00:10:49,640 --> 00:10:51,160
How thoughtful.

113
00:10:53,800 --> 00:10:55,240
But don't worry.

114
00:10:56,200 --> 00:10:57,040
No matter what,

115
00:10:58,880 --> 00:11:00,160
he'll definitely come.

116
00:11:27,200 --> 00:11:28,040
Yes?

117
00:11:28,640 --> 00:11:30,480
Mr. Samut still isn't here.

118
00:11:31,800 --> 00:11:33,680
<i>Should we tell the staff to replace you</i>

119
00:11:33,760 --> 00:11:35,560
with another pair for the finale?

120
00:11:36,160 --> 00:11:38,120
<i>Otherwise, we'll get fined heavily.</i>

121
00:11:44,200 --> 00:11:46,080
Hey, are you stunned?

122
00:11:46,640 --> 00:11:49,640
Then I'll tell Ms. Eve you're withdrawing.

123
00:11:52,440 --> 00:11:53,360
No.

124
00:11:53,880 --> 00:11:56,360
It's too late to fix anything now.

125
00:11:56,440 --> 00:11:58,200
<i>Then what are we going to do--</i>

126
00:12:00,200 --> 00:12:03,640
Oh? She hung up?

127
00:12:05,440 --> 00:12:08,000
Ms. May, Mr. Samut still hasn't arrived?

128
00:12:08,080 --> 00:12:09,840
You're next.

129
00:12:12,280 --> 00:12:13,600
I'll take responsibility myself.

130
00:12:16,560 --> 00:12:17,480
Please.

131
00:12:44,320 --> 00:12:45,440
Please proceed.

132
00:13:15,600 --> 00:13:17,560
Aren't they supposed to walk as a couple?

133
00:13:17,640 --> 00:13:19,200
Where's Mr. Mahasamut?

134
00:13:19,720 --> 00:13:23,320
Right. Did they fight or something?

135
00:13:24,400 --> 00:13:25,240
Beautiful.

136
00:13:45,720 --> 00:13:46,920
Excuse me.

137
00:13:53,640 --> 00:13:56,440
A bouquet and a card from Mr. Mahasamut.

138
00:14:24,160 --> 00:14:29,600
"My Precious, this bouquet
is my gratitude to the one

139
00:14:30,200 --> 00:14:32,080
who has always stood by my side.

140
00:14:32,600 --> 00:14:33,840
To my Maysa."

141
00:14:36,280 --> 00:14:37,800
So sweet.

142
00:14:37,880 --> 00:14:39,040
I'm jealous.

143
00:14:40,320 --> 00:14:42,680
Mr. Mahasamut is busy
with national matters.

144
00:14:43,880 --> 00:14:46,200
But even though he couldn't be here,

145
00:14:46,880 --> 00:14:49,880
he wanted this piece of art

146
00:14:50,560 --> 00:14:52,640
that represents his feelings

147
00:14:53,480 --> 00:14:55,120
to stand beside me

148
00:14:55,720 --> 00:14:57,600
at this prestigious event.

149
00:14:58,640 --> 00:15:01,880
- Wow.
- So sweet.

150
00:15:01,960 --> 00:15:03,040
Yes.

151
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:05,640
- This way, please.
- Ms. May.

152
00:15:06,680 --> 00:15:09,160
- So pretty.
- This way, please.

153
00:15:20,480 --> 00:15:24,560
I can't believe
Mr. Samut went all out like this.

154
00:15:25,760 --> 00:15:27,320
That's sexier than I expected.

155
00:15:30,200 --> 00:15:31,360
It wasn't him.

156
00:15:32,520 --> 00:15:34,800
What? Not Mr. Samut?

157
00:15:35,840 --> 00:15:37,720
Then who sent this?

158
00:15:48,240 --> 00:15:49,280
"Sincerely yours,

159
00:15:50,360 --> 00:15:51,440
V."

160
00:15:56,720 --> 00:15:57,920
Mr. Wayu?

161
00:16:00,280 --> 00:16:03,160
How did he even know you needed help?

162
00:16:06,600 --> 00:16:10,000
And when did you prepare this watch?

163
00:16:26,680 --> 00:16:28,320
If the man's watch is here,

164
00:16:29,160 --> 00:16:31,160
what about this one?

165
00:16:31,880 --> 00:16:34,320
Is it real or fake?

166
00:16:35,920 --> 00:16:36,960
Oh.

167
00:16:37,040 --> 00:16:39,440
It's real.

168
00:16:39,520 --> 00:16:42,080
He has this limited edition?

169
00:16:44,960 --> 00:16:47,240
What kind of high-class mafia son is this?

170
00:16:48,480 --> 00:16:49,760
I can't believe it.

171
00:16:51,000 --> 00:16:53,720
But he knows you're with Mr. Samut.

172
00:16:54,320 --> 00:16:55,800
Why go this far?

173
00:16:57,520 --> 00:16:58,800
What does he want?

174
00:17:19,359 --> 00:17:20,839
Hello, Mr. Wayu.

175
00:17:21,760 --> 00:17:25,640
How should I thank my benefactor
for helping me this much?

176
00:17:29,280 --> 00:17:32,960
I know you did it out of goodwill,

177
00:17:33,680 --> 00:17:35,720
but I should return the favor.

178
00:17:49,360 --> 00:17:50,360
I see.

179
00:17:51,720 --> 00:17:53,040
I'll think about it.

180
00:17:58,320 --> 00:18:00,040
Did he ask you to dinner?

181
00:18:02,800 --> 00:18:03,880
Or…

182
00:18:04,720 --> 00:18:06,320
something more?

183
00:18:20,040 --> 00:18:21,440
What did he send?

184
00:18:33,640 --> 00:18:37,160
You have to watch it. <i>Oppa</i> is so handsome,

185
00:18:37,240 --> 00:18:39,160
it makes my heart ache.

186
00:18:39,240 --> 00:18:40,200
Okay.

187
00:19:18,640 --> 00:19:21,560
Mr. Wayu, are you going
to be Mr. Dharn's rival now?

188
00:19:28,320 --> 00:19:29,160
Take it.

189
00:19:35,040 --> 00:19:35,920
Mr. Dharn sent them.

190
00:19:36,000 --> 00:19:37,080
What?

191
00:19:43,000 --> 00:19:44,560
You should've said that earlier.

192
00:19:50,480 --> 00:19:52,920
There's a card too.

193
00:19:55,360 --> 00:19:59,800
<i>Thank you for visiting me.</i>
<i>I felt much better because of you.</i>

194
00:20:00,480 --> 00:20:03,760
Why? Why?

195
00:20:03,840 --> 00:20:06,680
Why is a patient sending flowers

196
00:20:06,760 --> 00:20:08,240
to someone who's perfectly healthy?

197
00:20:08,320 --> 00:20:10,680
- Why? Why?
- He's probably

198
00:20:11,560 --> 00:20:14,640
apologizing about the news.

199
00:20:15,360 --> 00:20:18,480
But this will just make bigger news.

200
00:20:24,360 --> 00:20:25,680
Hey.

201
00:20:27,800 --> 00:20:29,560
How could you do that? That's rude.

202
00:20:34,160 --> 00:20:36,360
Hey!

203
00:20:38,960 --> 00:20:40,920
If your brother finds out,

204
00:20:41,000 --> 00:20:43,480
even ten trucks of apology flowers
wouldn't be enough.

205
00:21:03,640 --> 00:21:04,840
Hello?

206
00:21:06,200 --> 00:21:07,880
Hello?

207
00:21:09,760 --> 00:21:10,720
Something urgent?

208
00:21:17,160 --> 00:21:19,160
Uh, be careful.

209
00:21:21,080 --> 00:21:22,120
Slowly.

210
00:21:22,840 --> 00:21:25,120
Someone said they saw Mei
walk into this building.

211
00:21:25,200 --> 00:21:27,080
Oh my God. Why would she go in there?

212
00:21:27,160 --> 00:21:29,800
It's full of drug addicts.

213
00:21:30,800 --> 00:21:33,400
- Did you call the police?
- Yes, but they haven't arrived yet.

214
00:21:42,000 --> 00:21:44,720
I'll go in first. You stay here.

215
00:21:45,400 --> 00:21:46,320
Okay.

216
00:21:53,280 --> 00:21:56,480
- Is it going to be okay?
- It's fine.

217
00:22:18,720 --> 00:22:20,320
You're challenging me?

218
00:22:20,400 --> 00:22:22,360
Yeah, I am.

219
00:22:22,440 --> 00:22:24,080
Go ahead, hit me right here.

220
00:22:24,160 --> 00:22:26,680
Right here. You dare?
Or are you too scared?

221
00:22:32,000 --> 00:22:32,960
That didn't hurt.

222
00:22:34,320 --> 00:22:35,920
Is that all you've got?

223
00:22:37,080 --> 00:22:38,280
Kick me!

224
00:22:38,880 --> 00:22:40,400
Go on, kick me!

225
00:22:40,480 --> 00:22:42,120
You little--

226
00:22:46,880 --> 00:22:48,040
Come here.

227
00:22:49,040 --> 00:22:51,280
You piece of trash.
What were you doing to my sister?

228
00:22:51,360 --> 00:22:54,440
Your sister came to me herself.

229
00:22:54,520 --> 00:22:56,000
Crazy girl wanted to get beaten.

230
00:22:56,720 --> 00:22:59,040
Liar!

231
00:23:21,480 --> 00:23:24,680
- Oh.
- Mei.

232
00:23:24,760 --> 00:23:26,040
Are you okay?

233
00:23:27,560 --> 00:23:29,560
Why did you come here?

234
00:23:29,640 --> 00:23:33,160
You know this place is full of addicts.

235
00:23:33,240 --> 00:23:36,200
So they could rape me to death.

236
00:23:37,080 --> 00:23:38,640
You ungrateful child!

237
00:23:38,720 --> 00:23:40,520
Why are you doing this to spite me?

238
00:23:41,480 --> 00:23:43,200
Who is that man?

239
00:23:43,280 --> 00:23:44,920
Why won't you tell me?

240
00:23:46,680 --> 00:23:50,680
What am I supposed to do, Mei?

241
00:23:50,760 --> 00:23:52,960
What are you gonna do? Don't do anything!

242
00:23:53,680 --> 00:23:56,280
I'll go my way. I'll deal with it myself.

243
00:23:56,360 --> 00:23:57,200
I won't accept this!

244
00:23:57,800 --> 00:24:00,360
I'll make that man take responsibility!

245
00:24:00,440 --> 00:24:01,280
I won't let this go!

246
00:24:01,360 --> 00:24:04,000
- Mom.
- You can't!

247
00:24:04,080 --> 00:24:05,800
Mom, calm down.

248
00:24:05,880 --> 00:24:06,760
Auntie.

249
00:24:06,840 --> 00:24:08,320
Auntie, calm down.

250
00:24:08,400 --> 00:24:10,400
What karma is this?

251
00:24:10,480 --> 00:24:12,080
- Calm down, Mom.
- Calm down.

252
00:24:12,160 --> 00:24:14,160
Let's take Ms. Mei to the hospital first.

253
00:24:14,240 --> 00:24:15,880
Then we can talk things through, okay?

254
00:24:18,720 --> 00:24:20,200
Please calm down.

255
00:24:20,280 --> 00:24:23,160
Mei…

256
00:24:27,920 --> 00:24:31,920
Please give Mei some time.

257
00:24:32,000 --> 00:24:33,680
Don't pressure her yet.

258
00:24:34,200 --> 00:24:38,360
I'll try to find a way to talk to her
about getting treatment

259
00:24:38,440 --> 00:24:40,800
and make sure she doesn't
do anything dangerous again.

260
00:24:40,880 --> 00:24:45,760
Thank you so much
for taking Mei to the doctor

261
00:24:45,840 --> 00:24:47,600
and paying for her medicine.

262
00:24:47,680 --> 00:24:49,760
Thank you so, so much.

263
00:24:50,840 --> 00:24:51,880
It's really okay.

264
00:24:51,960 --> 00:24:53,800
That's what our foundation is here for.

265
00:24:54,320 --> 00:24:57,680
Please help talk to her for me.

266
00:24:57,760 --> 00:25:00,960
- Please.
- Of course, please go get some rest first.

267
00:25:01,040 --> 00:25:02,840
Thank you so much.

268
00:25:12,880 --> 00:25:13,760
Hey,

269
00:25:13,840 --> 00:25:16,440
let me talk to Ms. Mei alone for a moment.

270
00:25:18,760 --> 00:25:19,600
Yes.

271
00:25:28,640 --> 00:25:29,800
Ms. Mei.

272
00:25:32,720 --> 00:25:34,000
I'll talk to you later.

273
00:25:47,800 --> 00:25:49,360
Let me help you.

274
00:25:50,920 --> 00:25:53,000
I really want to listen
to what's troubling you.

275
00:25:57,040 --> 00:25:59,680
But if you're not ready
to talk right now, that's okay.

276
00:26:01,360 --> 00:26:04,240
If there's anything at all
you'd like me to help with, just tell me.

277
00:26:05,920 --> 00:26:08,520
What would a rich girl
like you understand?

278
00:26:17,120 --> 00:26:18,120
When I was little,

279
00:26:19,200 --> 00:26:21,600
I was kidnapped by a driver.

280
00:26:29,160 --> 00:26:31,200
He tried to cut off my hand.

281
00:26:36,720 --> 00:26:38,520
After that,

282
00:26:39,840 --> 00:26:41,880
I had to see a psychiatrist for years

283
00:26:43,160 --> 00:26:44,920
before I could go anywhere alone again.

284
00:26:50,120 --> 00:26:52,360
But once I got through it,

285
00:26:53,360 --> 00:26:55,520
there were two things I was thankful for.

286
00:26:56,880 --> 00:26:59,040
I wanted to thank
the person who helped me,

287
00:27:01,040 --> 00:27:02,480
and I wanted to thank myself

288
00:27:04,320 --> 00:27:06,080
for accepting that help.

289
00:27:08,040 --> 00:27:09,800
That's how I'm here today.

290
00:27:15,480 --> 00:27:17,360
Mom must hate me now.

291
00:27:20,680 --> 00:27:22,200
I made her so upset.

292
00:27:24,440 --> 00:27:26,200
She must be so disappointed in me.

293
00:27:28,120 --> 00:27:30,000
Am I going to hell?

294
00:27:32,280 --> 00:27:33,240
Ms. Mei,

295
00:27:34,360 --> 00:27:35,520
no matter

296
00:27:36,160 --> 00:27:38,760
what your mother says,
even if she complains or scolds you,

297
00:27:40,040 --> 00:27:41,760
she loves you so much.

298
00:27:42,920 --> 00:27:44,480
She's so worried about you.

299
00:27:45,240 --> 00:27:47,800
That's why she sent me to help you.

300
00:27:58,080 --> 00:27:59,000
It's okay.

301
00:28:06,320 --> 00:28:07,760
It's okay.

302
00:28:12,600 --> 00:28:14,560
You can still help your mom.

303
00:28:18,840 --> 00:28:21,800
You're trying to coax me into telling
my mom who the baby's father is, right?

304
00:28:22,920 --> 00:28:23,800
No.

305
00:28:25,680 --> 00:28:27,440
The way to help the people we love

306
00:28:28,640 --> 00:28:30,840
is to love ourselves
and care of ourselves first.

307
00:28:33,520 --> 00:28:35,280
If you make yourself okay again,

308
00:28:37,320 --> 00:28:39,320
the people you love will get better too.

309
00:28:43,600 --> 00:28:45,080
Take your time and think

310
00:28:46,000 --> 00:28:47,400
about what you want help with.

311
00:28:51,680 --> 00:28:53,680
<i>Oh.</i>

312
00:28:53,760 --> 00:28:55,760
That baby in her womb is seriously tough.

313
00:28:55,840 --> 00:28:58,360
Even after getting beaten like that,
it still made it.

314
00:28:59,440 --> 00:29:01,960
Even though the examination
didn't show anything abnormal,

315
00:29:02,040 --> 00:29:04,480
the doctor still said they need
to monitor her symptoms first.

316
00:29:06,720 --> 00:29:10,280
Ms. Mei's mother said she was close
with a senior at the factory.

317
00:29:11,600 --> 00:29:13,240
Apparently, he has a wife
and kids already.

318
00:29:14,000 --> 00:29:15,760
They suspect he might be the father.

319
00:29:18,920 --> 00:29:22,040
I also heard Ms. Mei
talking to someone on the phone.

320
00:29:24,320 --> 00:29:26,920
A man gets her pregnant
and then refuses to take responsibility?

321
00:29:27,000 --> 00:29:28,960
I say we go straight to his workplace.

322
00:29:29,040 --> 00:29:31,000
Yong, calm down first.

323
00:29:31,080 --> 00:29:34,680
We can't rush this. We need
to wait until she opens up more.

324
00:29:35,480 --> 00:29:38,760
And I told her mother and brother
to keep an eye on her.

325
00:29:40,000 --> 00:29:42,400
Ms. Mei is in
a very fragile state right now.

326
00:29:43,160 --> 00:29:44,760
I'm scared she might…

327
00:30:01,360 --> 00:30:03,040
What, Captain?

328
00:30:03,800 --> 00:30:05,880
Are you going back to investigate
the Jaiaree family case?

329
00:30:07,360 --> 00:30:08,400
Whoa, Captain…

330
00:30:08,480 --> 00:30:09,720
Whatever happens,

331
00:30:09,800 --> 00:30:12,480
Commander Singha already closed that case.

332
00:30:12,560 --> 00:30:15,720
But the statute of limitations hasn't
run out. There's still one year left.

333
00:30:15,800 --> 00:30:19,200
Wow, judging by that look,
you're not changing your mind, are you?

334
00:30:22,280 --> 00:30:25,680
Captain, Commander Singha
definitely won't approve.

335
00:30:27,640 --> 00:30:29,480
- Sergeant.
- Yes.

336
00:30:29,560 --> 00:30:32,120
You know you're the person
I trust the most, right?

337
00:30:33,880 --> 00:30:34,800
Yes.

338
00:30:36,440 --> 00:30:38,440
Then keep this a secret for me.

339
00:30:40,520 --> 00:30:42,480
Oh wow.

340
00:30:42,560 --> 00:30:44,400
Is it too late to stop
being trustworthy now?

341
00:30:44,480 --> 00:30:46,760
Too late.

342
00:30:46,840 --> 00:30:48,560
I'll buy you noodles.

343
00:30:48,640 --> 00:30:51,240
Oh wow, is that really worth it?
This could cost me my job.

344
00:30:55,560 --> 00:30:57,480
Captain, seriously,

345
00:30:58,440 --> 00:31:00,080
how are you even going
to investigate this?

346
00:31:00,880 --> 00:31:03,040
You know everyone from that family is…

347
00:31:05,800 --> 00:31:07,320
gone.

348
00:31:11,760 --> 00:31:14,280
But not all
of the victims' relatives are gone.

349
00:31:17,360 --> 00:31:19,720
Back then, your father, Mr. Prakat,

350
00:31:19,800 --> 00:31:22,600
was the neighbor of the Jaiaree family,

351
00:31:23,120 --> 00:31:24,600
and he also died in the fire.

352
00:31:25,760 --> 00:31:27,840
I'd like to ask for more information.

353
00:31:30,080 --> 00:31:32,320
But it's been six years already.

354
00:31:32,400 --> 00:31:35,120
And I already told the police
everything back then.

355
00:31:35,200 --> 00:31:37,840
Yes. I've read your statement.

356
00:31:38,720 --> 00:31:41,960
It says that that night,

357
00:31:42,480 --> 00:31:43,800
you went to bed early,

358
00:31:44,960 --> 00:31:46,720
so you didn't know
your father wasn't home.

359
00:31:47,640 --> 00:31:49,440
Then you woke up
in the middle of the night,

360
00:31:50,720 --> 00:31:52,680
saw that house on fire,

361
00:31:53,440 --> 00:31:55,200
and went looking for your father,

362
00:31:56,120 --> 00:31:59,040
only to find his body there.

363
00:32:03,400 --> 00:32:04,320
Yes.

364
00:32:06,680 --> 00:32:08,480
But before the fire started,

365
00:32:09,360 --> 00:32:10,920
several gunshots were heard.

366
00:32:12,400 --> 00:32:15,800
Your statement says
you were asleep and didn't hear them.

367
00:32:17,880 --> 00:32:18,720
The shots were fired

368
00:32:19,800 --> 00:32:22,640
less than ten minutes
before the fire broke out.

369
00:32:24,400 --> 00:32:26,360
So what woke you up

370
00:32:26,440 --> 00:32:27,800
and made you notice the fire?

371
00:32:30,280 --> 00:32:31,240
I…

372
00:32:33,080 --> 00:32:36,720
I really can't remember
why I woke up then.

373
00:32:37,800 --> 00:32:40,320
I'm sorry to ask. It's just that

374
00:32:40,400 --> 00:32:42,680
I noticed the officers
never asked about this part,

375
00:32:42,760 --> 00:32:44,840
so I wanted a little more detail.

376
00:32:48,080 --> 00:32:49,800
Please think carefully.

377
00:32:50,880 --> 00:32:52,840
Are you sure you didn't
hear anything at all?

378
00:32:53,520 --> 00:32:54,800
Or

379
00:32:56,560 --> 00:32:57,720
did you hear something,

380
00:32:59,880 --> 00:33:02,040
but because of the gunshots,
you ignored it?

381
00:33:06,520 --> 00:33:07,960
I really didn't hear anything.

382
00:33:08,960 --> 00:33:11,920
And I can't remember why I woke up either.

383
00:33:13,520 --> 00:33:14,920
Maybe I was thirsty?

384
00:33:15,920 --> 00:33:19,240
No matter how many times you ask,
that's all I can tell you.

385
00:33:20,960 --> 00:33:23,600
I don't have any other answers for you.

386
00:33:23,680 --> 00:33:25,160
Please leave.

387
00:33:27,760 --> 00:33:28,680
Thank you.

388
00:33:48,520 --> 00:33:49,560
Hello?

389
00:33:50,360 --> 00:33:51,960
This is Aemika,

390
00:33:52,960 --> 00:33:54,520
Mr. Prakat's daughter.

391
00:33:55,440 --> 00:33:58,440
Has the case been reopened?

392
00:33:59,160 --> 00:34:01,520
Why is Captain Anawin tracking down

393
00:34:01,600 --> 00:34:04,240
the neighbor's daughter
who got caught up in the Jaiaree case?

394
00:34:05,000 --> 00:34:06,880
Why isn't he investigating Black Doc?

395
00:34:08,719 --> 00:34:09,840
Should I keep following him?

396
00:34:13,600 --> 00:34:15,719
Yes. But send someone else.

397
00:34:15,800 --> 00:34:17,120
I don't want him getting suspicious.

398
00:34:18,280 --> 00:34:20,480
Here.

399
00:34:22,199 --> 00:34:23,440
Your pay.

400
00:34:25,120 --> 00:34:27,040
It's nothing, miss. No need.

401
00:34:27,120 --> 00:34:28,080
No.

402
00:34:29,120 --> 00:34:32,000
You were tailing a special
investigations officer. That's risky.

403
00:34:33,040 --> 00:34:34,080
Alright then.

404
00:34:36,199 --> 00:34:37,760
I'll take my leave.

405
00:34:48,040 --> 00:34:49,400
Captain Anawin,

406
00:34:50,199 --> 00:34:51,800
what are you really up to?

407
00:34:51,880 --> 00:34:54,760
Captain, there's a new restaurant
opening in the alley nearby.

408
00:34:54,840 --> 00:34:59,000
I heard the waitresses there
are absolutely stunning.

409
00:34:59,080 --> 00:35:01,280
So I was wondering,

410
00:35:01,360 --> 00:35:04,160
would you be interested
in treating us there?

411
00:35:04,840 --> 00:35:08,600
You guys go ahead. I've got no time.
Still not done with my work.

412
00:35:08,680 --> 00:35:10,640
Whoa.

413
00:35:12,840 --> 00:35:14,080
Hello. Hello.

414
00:35:17,360 --> 00:35:19,720
Ah, now I get it.

415
00:35:19,800 --> 00:35:22,960
I finally understand why the Captain
doesn't have time for us.

416
00:35:24,160 --> 00:35:27,640
Sergeant, it's not like that.

417
00:35:27,720 --> 00:35:29,480
Between Ms. Prapai and me…

418
00:35:29,560 --> 00:35:30,960
there's nothing.

419
00:35:31,040 --> 00:35:33,120
Wow, rejecting me that fast?

420
00:35:33,200 --> 00:35:35,240
You're hurting my self-esteem.

421
00:35:36,400 --> 00:35:38,920
Don't misunderstand. It's not like that.

422
00:35:39,000 --> 00:35:42,040
I didn't mean you're not good enough.
It's just that I…

423
00:35:42,120 --> 00:35:43,720
Alright, Captain, calm down.

424
00:35:43,800 --> 00:35:45,920
We'll head out first,

425
00:35:46,000 --> 00:35:48,440
so we're not third wheels.

426
00:35:49,440 --> 00:35:50,920
- Come on, guys.
- Sergeant.

427
00:35:51,800 --> 00:35:53,200
- Sergeant Dam.
- Yes?

428
00:35:53,280 --> 00:35:54,640
- Wait.
- Take your time.

429
00:36:10,000 --> 00:36:11,160
Are you having fun?

430
00:36:13,520 --> 00:36:16,360
So, what brings you here?

431
00:36:16,880 --> 00:36:20,880
Oh, I just happened to be in the area,
so I dropped by

432
00:36:20,960 --> 00:36:22,280
to give you this discount.

433
00:36:24,840 --> 00:36:27,080
It's a health check package for dogs,

434
00:36:27,160 --> 00:36:28,520
15 items included.

435
00:36:28,600 --> 00:36:31,520
I'm telling you, you won't find
a cheaper deal anywhere.

436
00:36:32,960 --> 00:36:35,640
If you don't believe me, go check.

437
00:36:35,720 --> 00:36:38,360
Other places charge at least 4,000 baht.

438
00:36:38,440 --> 00:36:40,480
And for your dog,

439
00:36:40,560 --> 00:36:43,400
a Golden Retriever over five years old,

440
00:36:44,080 --> 00:36:46,920
this price is extremely affordable.

441
00:36:50,680 --> 00:36:53,200
Plus, you don't even have to wait there.

442
00:36:53,280 --> 00:36:56,720
Our hospital provides free pickup
and drop-off service.

443
00:36:56,800 --> 00:36:58,920
Safe and convenient.

444
00:37:05,800 --> 00:37:07,360
Is something wrong?

445
00:37:12,560 --> 00:37:13,560
But…

446
00:37:15,520 --> 00:37:16,600
I'm…

447
00:37:17,360 --> 00:37:18,920
curious about one thing.

448
00:37:20,800 --> 00:37:21,880
Well…

449
00:37:25,840 --> 00:37:26,680
How did you know

450
00:37:27,800 --> 00:37:31,840
my dog is a Golden over five years old?

451
00:37:38,680 --> 00:37:42,320
- Oh, well, I mean…
- Well?

452
00:37:44,280 --> 00:37:47,120
- Well…
- How did you know?

453
00:37:49,440 --> 00:37:51,720
I'm asking you. How did you know?

454
00:37:55,880 --> 00:37:56,920
What are you doing?

455
00:37:57,000 --> 00:37:59,480
Are you trying to harass me?

456
00:38:04,320 --> 00:38:05,840
This is the evidence.

457
00:38:08,040 --> 00:38:09,080
It's your dog's fur.

458
00:38:16,920 --> 00:38:18,520
I noticed it a while ago.

459
00:38:18,600 --> 00:38:20,240
One look and I knew.

460
00:38:20,320 --> 00:38:22,800
Smooth-colored fur,
no patterns, water-resistant.

461
00:38:23,720 --> 00:38:25,800
Golden Retriever fur around the legs,

462
00:38:25,880 --> 00:38:30,040
underbelly, and tail flows like feathers.

463
00:38:30,120 --> 00:38:33,280
I'd say this came from when your dog

464
00:38:33,360 --> 00:38:35,920
jumped up with its front paws on your hip.

465
00:38:36,000 --> 00:38:37,440
How do you know that?

466
00:38:38,560 --> 00:38:39,960
Because I'm good at what I do.

467
00:38:40,560 --> 00:38:42,080
Think about it,

468
00:38:42,160 --> 00:38:45,200
if I can tell all that just from fur,

469
00:38:45,880 --> 00:38:47,800
imagine how much I'd know

470
00:38:48,560 --> 00:38:49,920
if you brought your dog in.

471
00:38:54,600 --> 00:38:55,800
If you don't want to, that's fine.

472
00:38:56,400 --> 00:38:57,880
But don't regret it later.

473
00:39:07,320 --> 00:39:08,360
Bye.

474
00:39:16,720 --> 00:39:20,600
ANAWIN PIPATPONG

475
00:39:48,520 --> 00:39:51,760
Did you think I'd come?

476
00:39:56,120 --> 00:39:57,960
Have you ever gambled?

477
00:40:00,720 --> 00:40:02,440
Hasn't everyone?

478
00:40:03,400 --> 00:40:05,200
It's like gambling.

479
00:40:05,840 --> 00:40:08,080
I consider every possibility.

480
00:40:11,120 --> 00:40:13,680
Including that limited-edition watch?

481
00:40:17,120 --> 00:40:20,640
Everyone knows
that at that launch event,

482
00:40:20,720 --> 00:40:22,600
only the brand owner

483
00:40:23,240 --> 00:40:27,120
and a few VIP guests could wear it.

484
00:40:27,640 --> 00:40:29,240
Anything's possible.

485
00:40:32,000 --> 00:40:34,400
You don't need to worry
about how I got it.

486
00:40:36,880 --> 00:40:39,400
But that day, you looked beautiful.

487
00:40:40,320 --> 00:40:42,680
Like one of my favorite actresses,

488
00:40:44,000 --> 00:40:44,960
Emma Stone.

489
00:40:54,960 --> 00:40:57,480
You've watched it like ten times.
Still into it?

490
00:41:02,200 --> 00:41:03,880
Emma Stone is amazing.

491
00:41:03,960 --> 00:41:06,720
I never get bored of her.

492
00:41:08,080 --> 00:41:09,760
Do you know Maysa?

493
00:41:10,800 --> 00:41:12,320
Maysa Jaiaree.

494
00:41:12,400 --> 00:41:13,560
She's even better.

495
00:41:16,440 --> 00:41:20,840
I'll make you more famous than Emma Stone.

496
00:41:23,480 --> 00:41:27,320
Wake up. Stop dreaming so big.

497
00:41:27,400 --> 00:41:30,160
You can't even take me to the beach yet.

498
00:41:31,080 --> 00:41:32,600
How many times have you postponed it?

499
00:41:33,240 --> 00:41:36,280
I've been busy studying.
Exams after exams.

500
00:41:36,360 --> 00:41:38,040
I don't even have time to breathe.

501
00:41:40,160 --> 00:41:42,640
Once I graduate, I'll take you right away.

502
00:41:43,520 --> 00:41:44,760
Where do you want to go?

503
00:42:05,080 --> 00:42:08,000
I want to go the place we first met.

504
00:42:09,680 --> 00:42:13,960
I want to watch the sunset there with you.

505
00:42:15,840 --> 00:42:17,600
I'll graduate,

506
00:42:17,680 --> 00:42:19,240
start working,

507
00:42:19,320 --> 00:42:21,080
and buy a house there for you,

508
00:42:21,160 --> 00:42:24,680
so you can watch the sunrise
and sunset all you want.

509
00:42:28,800 --> 00:42:30,600
I love you the most.

510
00:42:31,240 --> 00:42:32,480
I love you the most.

511
00:42:38,480 --> 00:42:41,280
The sunset here is the most beautiful.

512
00:42:50,360 --> 00:42:51,720
Really?

513
00:43:51,560 --> 00:43:53,400
Are you done yet? I want to take some too.

514
00:44:05,080 --> 00:44:06,520
There are plenty of spots.

515
00:44:10,360 --> 00:44:11,600
I want this exact spot.

516
00:44:12,200 --> 00:44:13,680
The sunset looks the best from here.

517
00:44:17,040 --> 00:44:20,080
Then come sit next to me.

518
00:44:20,160 --> 00:44:21,560
No.

519
00:44:22,360 --> 00:44:24,800
I want this frame.
You need to move out of my shot.

520
00:44:25,720 --> 00:44:28,640
What? Why should I move?

521
00:44:29,720 --> 00:44:31,520
Because my composition
won't work otherwise.

522
00:44:31,600 --> 00:44:33,040
I came here before to shoot a drama.

523
00:44:33,120 --> 00:44:35,680
The director set the frame here,
and I think it looks beautiful,

524
00:44:35,760 --> 00:44:37,800
so I want a photo here too.

525
00:44:45,080 --> 00:44:46,560
Are you an actress?

526
00:44:48,480 --> 00:44:50,880
Of course. What, you think I'm lying?

527
00:44:52,520 --> 00:44:53,680
I don't believe you.

528
00:44:54,880 --> 00:44:56,560
Let me see your Instagram first.

529
00:45:02,040 --> 00:45:05,560
"Maybe.maysa." M-A-Y-B-E dot M-A-Y-S-A.

530
00:45:05,640 --> 00:45:07,160
Mine's Peeraka.

531
00:45:07,240 --> 00:45:10,480
"Peeraka.j." P-E-E-R-A-K-A dot J.

532
00:45:11,920 --> 00:45:12,840
Who asked?

533
00:45:21,760 --> 00:45:23,080
A medical student?

534
00:45:24,000 --> 00:45:26,040
Whoa, she's actually an actress.

535
00:46:26,560 --> 00:46:27,840
Is something wrong?

536
00:46:32,960 --> 00:46:33,840
No.

537
00:46:36,440 --> 00:46:38,200
This place is still as beautiful as ever.

538
00:46:40,840 --> 00:46:42,320
You've been here before?

539
00:46:44,120 --> 00:46:46,200
Not many people check in here.

540
00:46:47,560 --> 00:46:49,200
I thought I could surprise you.

541
00:47:04,880 --> 00:47:06,360
I came here a long time ago.

542
00:47:07,400 --> 00:47:08,760
Maybe seven or eight years ago.

543
00:47:08,840 --> 00:47:09,960
This is

544
00:47:11,000 --> 00:47:13,040
the best spot to watch the sunset.

545
00:47:19,760 --> 00:47:21,520
You look happy.

546
00:47:24,200 --> 00:47:25,720
It must be a good memory.

547
00:47:28,240 --> 00:47:29,840
You weren't alone back then, right?

548
00:47:33,680 --> 00:47:34,600
No.

549
00:47:36,840 --> 00:47:38,560
I was here with someone.

550
00:47:45,720 --> 00:47:47,080
It wasn't Mr. Samut, right?

551
00:47:52,200 --> 00:47:54,000
I'm kind of jealous of that guy.

552
00:48:10,760 --> 00:48:12,280
But that's all in the past now.

553
00:48:13,240 --> 00:48:14,280
Because right now,

554
00:48:16,200 --> 00:48:17,040
I'm here.

555
00:48:18,000 --> 00:48:20,720
RIght here, with you.

556
00:49:11,680 --> 00:49:12,640
Hello?

557
00:49:15,280 --> 00:49:16,600
See you in two hours.

558
00:49:20,600 --> 00:49:21,440
Urgent work?

559
00:49:24,480 --> 00:49:26,360
Should we head back then?

560
00:49:44,640 --> 00:49:45,560
May.

561
00:49:47,200 --> 00:49:50,680
Is that May? May!

562
00:49:50,760 --> 00:49:53,560
May. That's her.
Let's go take a picture with her.

563
00:50:05,400 --> 00:50:06,520
Hey.

564
00:50:06,600 --> 00:50:08,960
What May are you talking about?
That's a couple kissing.

565
00:50:09,040 --> 00:50:11,000
You still want to go ask for an autograph?

566
00:50:11,080 --> 00:50:13,880
How would I know?
I don't have perfect eyesight.

567
00:50:13,960 --> 00:50:17,840
- I thought it was her.
- Then why run your mouth if you can't see?

568
00:50:17,920 --> 00:50:20,400
- Come here, you old hag!
- You're the old hag.

569
00:50:20,480 --> 00:50:21,760
- Annoying.
- Come here.

570
00:50:32,040 --> 00:50:33,240
You're safe now.

571
00:50:38,920 --> 00:50:40,440
I'm sorry for startling you.

572
00:50:42,920 --> 00:50:44,600
I just didn't want you
to get into trouble.

573
00:50:48,560 --> 00:50:51,080
It's okay.

574
00:50:54,600 --> 00:50:57,080
Let's go. Someone might see us.

575
00:50:57,800 --> 00:50:58,880
Okay.

576
00:51:08,400 --> 00:51:11,560
Chok is going to take me
to live upcountry with him.

577
00:51:14,400 --> 00:51:15,480
Ms. Mei…

578
00:51:15,560 --> 00:51:19,200
I know you might not
feel comfortable hearing this.

579
00:51:23,080 --> 00:51:24,280
But he'll take care of me.

580
00:51:26,400 --> 00:51:28,320
We've thought it through.

581
00:51:32,360 --> 00:51:33,720
I came here

582
00:51:33,800 --> 00:51:36,040
because I wanted to tell you

583
00:51:36,760 --> 00:51:38,320
that you made me realize

584
00:51:39,360 --> 00:51:41,600
that instead of drowning in pain,

585
00:51:41,680 --> 00:51:43,640
at least

586
00:51:43,720 --> 00:51:46,160
I should get up and help myself.

587
00:51:47,520 --> 00:51:52,120
Maybe one day I'll get better.

588
00:51:52,680 --> 00:51:53,760
Like you.

589
00:51:59,840 --> 00:52:02,120
Thank you so much, Ms. Fahsai.

590
00:52:05,200 --> 00:52:06,440
Of course.

591
00:52:07,880 --> 00:52:08,800
But…

592
00:52:11,680 --> 00:52:15,760
there's one more thing
I want your help with.

593
00:52:19,680 --> 00:52:20,640
Well…

594
00:52:24,760 --> 00:52:25,600
Samut.

595
00:52:27,920 --> 00:52:30,520
Didn't Yong tell you I have a guest?

596
00:52:33,000 --> 00:52:34,200
She did.

597
00:52:34,280 --> 00:52:36,280
But I have something important to discuss.

598
00:52:39,800 --> 00:52:41,600
May I cut in?

599
00:52:42,440 --> 00:52:43,280
Sure.

600
00:52:45,040 --> 00:52:47,120
It's okay. I can wait.

601
00:52:57,000 --> 00:52:58,760
I want you to work at the party.

602
00:53:00,000 --> 00:53:01,280
What about the foundation?

603
00:53:02,520 --> 00:53:05,280
Let Yong handle the foundation for now.

604
00:53:07,880 --> 00:53:10,280
If you're worried
I'll work with Mr. Dharn,

605
00:53:11,640 --> 00:53:12,960
don't be.

606
00:53:13,040 --> 00:53:15,000
I won't work with him.

607
00:53:15,640 --> 00:53:18,000
But I want to continue working here.

608
00:53:21,480 --> 00:53:22,720
I've made myself clear.

609
00:53:25,800 --> 00:53:27,440
I'd like to continue talking to Ms. Mei.

610
00:53:40,040 --> 00:53:43,440
I admit I'm worried about Dharn.

611
00:53:44,920 --> 00:53:49,320
But I want you at the party
because I really need your help.

612
00:53:52,400 --> 00:53:54,680
I just want to protect your reputation.

613
00:53:56,400 --> 00:53:58,960
But people misunderstood me,

614
00:53:59,960 --> 00:54:02,080
and now it's affecting our voter base.

615
00:54:05,480 --> 00:54:09,240
If you work with me, people will see
we're not at odds.

616
00:54:15,400 --> 00:54:16,240
Hey.

617
00:54:25,440 --> 00:54:29,040
Everything Dad, I, and the party built…

618
00:54:30,240 --> 00:54:32,720
I don't want it ruined because of me.

619
00:54:34,200 --> 00:54:35,360
Please.

620
00:54:36,880 --> 00:54:38,080
Please help me.

621
00:54:40,960 --> 00:54:43,680
Fahsai, come on, please help me.

622
00:55:12,480 --> 00:55:13,680
Your coffee.

623
00:55:19,240 --> 00:55:22,480
I'm discussing something important
with my sister.

624
00:55:24,200 --> 00:55:25,200
Yes.

625
00:55:28,360 --> 00:55:29,760
Tell Ms. Mei to come back in.

626
00:55:32,360 --> 00:55:34,200
I need time to think.

627
00:55:46,480 --> 00:55:48,200
You want the foundation
to act as a middleman

628
00:55:48,280 --> 00:55:50,120
to communicate with your family?

629
00:55:50,200 --> 00:55:51,240
Yes.

630
00:55:52,520 --> 00:55:55,440
It's easier through someone else.

631
00:55:57,200 --> 00:56:00,040
And right now, my mom is still very angry.

632
00:56:00,760 --> 00:56:03,680
This way, it might hurt less.

633
00:56:05,840 --> 00:56:06,840
Of course.

634
00:56:07,680 --> 00:56:09,000
For my new address,

635
00:56:09,080 --> 00:56:11,240
I'll let you know later.

636
00:56:12,280 --> 00:56:14,000
But please don't tell anyone yet,

637
00:56:16,000 --> 00:56:17,120
not even my mom.

638
00:56:19,320 --> 00:56:21,080
If my mom finds out,

639
00:56:22,080 --> 00:56:23,360
he…

640
00:56:26,120 --> 00:56:27,000
will know too.

641
00:56:33,160 --> 00:56:35,080
I need to go now.

642
00:56:40,440 --> 00:56:43,600
Alright. I wish you both the best.

643
00:56:44,480 --> 00:56:46,400
If you need anything,
you can always contact me.

644
00:56:47,200 --> 00:56:48,080
Yes.

645
00:56:57,680 --> 00:56:58,880
Is something wrong?

646
00:57:08,080 --> 00:57:09,480
Be careful…

647
00:57:14,680 --> 00:57:16,560
Take care of yourself.

648
00:57:19,560 --> 00:57:20,480
Alright.

649
00:57:31,400 --> 00:57:32,440
Goodbye.

650
00:57:41,120 --> 00:57:43,200
Starting tomorrow,
I'll be working at the party.

651
00:58:13,640 --> 00:58:15,000
Hey.

652
00:58:18,440 --> 00:58:20,120
We're already this far out of Bangkok?

653
00:58:20,200 --> 00:58:22,200
Where are you taking me?

654
00:58:22,960 --> 00:58:24,560
Wanna try racing with a substitute?

655
00:58:31,360 --> 00:58:32,480
Wow.

656
00:58:33,520 --> 00:58:34,720
This is so beautiful.

657
00:58:34,800 --> 00:58:37,120
I told you to guard him!

658
00:58:37,200 --> 00:58:38,160
Protect him!

659
00:58:38,240 --> 00:58:41,400
Find a doctor
who can keep their mouth shut

660
00:58:41,480 --> 00:58:42,400
and treat him.

661
00:58:43,040 --> 00:58:45,760
Can you find Black Doc for me?

662
00:58:45,840 --> 00:58:47,560
While you're operating on Aung Khin,

663
00:58:47,640 --> 00:58:49,880
I'll hack the feed
and play this video for them.

664
00:58:49,960 --> 00:58:51,960
<i>That means you'll only have as much time</i>

665
00:58:52,040 --> 00:58:53,640
<i>as the video runs.</i>

666
00:58:53,720 --> 00:58:55,760
<i>And once it ends,</i>
<i>it cuts back to real-time.</i>

667
00:58:55,840 --> 00:58:57,160
<i>So no matter what,</i>

668
00:58:57,240 --> 00:58:59,040
<i>you have to finish before the video ends.</i>

669
00:58:59,120 --> 00:59:00,720
There's only a few seconds left.

670
00:59:01,680 --> 00:59:03,280
There's no way he'll make it.

671
00:59:03,360 --> 00:59:05,960
Once the video ends,
they'll find out for sure.

672
01:00:01,600 --> 01:00:04,760
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
